# OpenSIPS Dispatcher List — FreeSWITCH Cluster
# Format: setid destination [flags [priority [attrs]]]
# Flags: 0=active, 2=disabled, 8=auto-probing
# 
# Group 1: FreeSWITCH Nodes (Auto-discovered from Kubernetes headless service)
# In K8s, these IPs are resolved from the StatefulSet headless service.
# Update these IPs to match your FreeSWITCH pod IPs or use DNS.
#
# setid  destination                        flags  priority  attrs
1        sip:freeswitch-0.freeswitch-hs.voip-core.svc.cluster.local:5080  0  10  node=fs-0
1        sip:freeswitch-1.freeswitch-hs.voip-core.svc.cluster.local:5080  0  10  node=fs-1
1        sip:freeswitch-2.freeswitch-hs.voip-core.svc.cluster.local:5080  0  10  node=fs-2

# Group 2: Human Agent SIP endpoints (MicroSIP / Softphone destinations)
# These are registered dynamically via SIP REGISTER
# Add static human agent URIs here if needed
# 2  sip:agent1@10.0.0.5:5060  0  10  agent=human-1
